About this item

  • Aeotec’s smallest, best-certified smart plug built with Gen7, Z-Wave Plus, S2, and SmartStart. 30% smaller than past smart switches at only 2.4x1.5x1.2 inch - so small that it doesn’t block other power outlets!
  • 99% accurate energy metering inbuilt. Analyses how much electricity you’re spending in real-time and reports it back to Z-Wave gateway software.
  • Z-Wave Plus, 700 series, and Z-Wave S2 certified for 30% quicker response time, 150% better wireless range, and 3-layers wireless security encryption. Z-Wave certification number: ZC12-20050064.
  • Inbuilt surge protector: protects your electronics from surges / spikes that are up to 2,000 volts. Inbuilt over-current protection up to 16 amps.
  • Compatible with certified Z-Wave gateways. Tested to work with Aetoec AutoPilot, Aeotec Smart Home Hub, Samsung SmartThings, Hubitat, Vera, ISY994i ZW and more.

Product Description

ZWave smart plug compatible with SmartThings


Aeotec makes quality connexions

Founded in 2006 as Aeon Labs in Silicon Valley, Aeotec has long focussed its craft on the intelligent automation of electronics through sensor and data driven decision making. We look at a home and imagine how it can be better through technology. Then we work to make it happen. Friendly and professional support team are at your service 24/5, More details, just kindly tell us

Aeotec Smart Switch 7.

Smarter. Safest. Smaller still.

  • Plug it. Automate it. Control it. And understand how much electricity you are spending. Smart Switch 7 - Aeotec’s smallest smart plug ever, is also everyone’s safest.
  • Intelligence is in control. Appliances turn on when needed and off when not. On a schedule. Or intelligently automated and triggered when needed.
  • With its enhanced antenna design and use of Z-Wave and S2, Smart Switch 7’s wireless signal reaches up to 492 foot in real-world use and now communicates and responds 50% faster.

Smallest, safest, Gen7 smart plug for Z-Wave.

Safety first.

Smart Switch 7 protects your electronics, your home, and your family. Inbuilt surge protection is certified to 2,000 volts, protecting appliances from spikes, surges, and overloads. Smart Switch 7 has been crafted and certified to FCC and ETL USA standards, making it the best-certified and safest smart plug available with Gen7 Z-Wave.

Control up to 15 amps.

Aeotec Z wave Smart Switch 7 can power devices that draw up to 15 amps of power. But safety comes first, so Smart Switch 7 is engineered with an inbuilt over-current protection that protects your home and its electronics at up to 16 amps.

Scheduling and manual control.

Electronics don’t have to be turned on all the time, just when we use them. Smart Switch 7 lets you automatically turn appliances on or off according to a schedule, via intelligent automation, or on-demand via compatible apps, remote controls, and voice-control systems connected to your smart-home automation hub.

Monitor and save your spending.

Smart Switch 7 accurately measures electricity you’re spending, reporting it back to your Z-Wave gateway in real-time and with 99% accuracy. You’ll be able to record, measure, and assess which appliances are turned on, how much they are costing you, and then create a schedule to reduce your electricity bill.

Simple to install.

Itʼs all-powerful but all simple. Smart Switch 7 takes only moments to install. With a SmartStart enabled gateway, you can connect it to your Z-Wave hub by simply scanning its QR code. From there, plug it into any power outlet in your home and that outlet is instantly smarter and ready for wireless automation.

1.2 inch height: doesn’t block outlets.

It’s more than a little annoying when power sockets are blocked by other electronics. Smart Switch 7 has been engineered to reduce that very possibility. At only 1.2 inches in height, Smart Switch 7 has been crafted to not block or crowd power sockets and boards.

ZWave hub required

Smart Switch 7 uses Z-Wave Plus to communicate wirelessly. That means you'll need a Z-Wave hub to use it.

Visit aeotec.com/z-wave-gateways/compatibility.html to find out which hubs Smart Switch 7 is compatible with. Compatible gateways include Aeotec AutoPilot, Aeotec Smart Home Hub, Home Assistant with Z-Stick Gen5+, HomeSeer, Hubitat, and SmartThings.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

  • Pepe
    5.0 out of 5 stars It's an awesome z-wave smart plug!
    Reviewed in the United States on February 16, 2021
    Verified Purchase
    Hello there,

    Ok, I love Aeotec products and they are one of the main reasons I use z-wave devices. I have many of their toys but today I just want to talk about the SmartSwitches since I have 35 of it's older little brother, the 6 series, I bought my very first Smart Switch 7 to give it a try so, let's dig into it at once!

    This device looks awesome and I don't think you will face any challenge putting two in the same outlet. I don't have two of these 7 series so I tested it sharing the outlets with a series 6.

    Somehow this smart switch feels a little bit cheaper and lacks the USB port the old 6 series had and I think it gets a little bit warm but other than that, it looks like a killer product and I'm starting to love it. If you already have a series 6 and wonders if this little plug that could is worth it, I seriously believe it does!!!

    So far I tested successfully on (see the pictures):

    ISY994i ZW+ IR/Pro
    Hubitat Elevation
    HomeSeer HS4 using an Aeotec Z-Stick Gen5

    It works out of the box with all of the above. I had some challenges on HS4 with Authenticated S2 security but none of the other two supports that mode so to be fair, I can say it works on all of them. I just used S0 on HS4, the other two well... the default which incidentally is S0 anyways :D

    Perhaps you may want to tweak the parameters 20 and 21 which handles the minimum threshold for Watts and Kwh to be reported automatically.

    In short, if you are in the market looking for a small smart switch that will handle your coffee machine at 1500+ Watts (I tested it with my ECM Technika IV)... this is a great option. Most of the smart plugs will die at 1000W or even less.

    Hope you find this information useful.

    3.0 out of 5 stars Turns off/on randomly
    Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
    Verified Purchase
    I use 2 of these with an Aeotec smart home hub (SmartThings). They pair very easily through the SmartThings app and are very responsive when manually turning on & off. The power meter is a value add, too.

    The problem with these, and I don't know if it's the hub or the switches, is that they will randomly turn off & then back on. I hear the relays click twice in fast succession. Nothing is shown in device logs, though.

    Normally, this isn't a problem for lights but if you're controlling larger appliances (or just to see the power consumption), this can cause problems. I have one connected to a computer and the off/on behavior causes it to restart.

    The off/on behavior happens every 1-2 days on each switch.

    I don't know if this is a hub problem or a switch problem but it's certainly something that subtracted 2 scores from my rating.
